        "observe": {
          "stage": "observe",
          "report": "OBSERVE STAGE: Verified all 22 review issues against source code.\n\n## Already Fixed (7 false-positives)\n\n[review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::runtime_value_in_types_module] false-positive: accentColors moved to src/lib/constants.ts, types/index.ts is now pure types.\n\n[review::.::holistic::high_level_elegance::runtime_value_in_types_module] false-positive: same fix as above, accentColors no longer in types module.\n\n[review::.::holistic::package_organization::types_dir_mixes_runtime] false-positive: same fix, types/index.ts has no runtime values.\n\n[review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::type_guard_contract_gap] false-positive: isRepoResponse now checks all 4 fields (stargazers_count, open_issues_count, updated_at, language) with correct typeof checks at lines 29-38.\n\n[review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::incomplete_type_guard] false-positive: duplicate of contract_coherence issue above, guard is complete.\n\n[review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::sequential_commits_fetch] false-positive: commits fetch is already in Promise.all at line 60 as 4th element.\n\n[review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::artefact_hardcoded_owner_url] false-positive: Artefacts.svelte uses https://github.com/{artefact.repo} and artefacts.ts has full owner/repo paths.\n\n## Exaggerated (3 issues)\n\n[review::.::holistic::logic_clarity::parseCommitCount_redundant_param] exaggerated: responseOk distinguishes no-response (0) from response-without-Link-header (1 commit). Not redundant. Minor: rename to responseReceived.\n\n[review::.::holistic::design_coherence::page_svelte_mixed_concerns] exaggerated: 85 lines of script for a single-page app composition root. Three concerns is appropriate; extracting increases file count without proportional benefit.\n\n[review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::duplicated_observer_pattern] exaggerated: two $effect blocks use IntersectionObserver with different options and callbacks. Extracting a helper for 2 uses is over-engineering.\n\n## Genuine (12 issues)\n\n[review::.::holistic::error_consistency::broad_catch_no_discrimination] genuine: fetchGitHub lines 6-14 returns null for both non-ok HTTP and caught exceptions. No distinction between 404, 403, or network failure. Add console.warn with status/error.\n\n[review::.::holistic::error_consistency::silent_error_swallowing] genuine: catch block line 11-12 is bare. Build-time SSG makes failures invisible. Add console.warn.\n\n[review::.::holistic::type_safety::fetchJson_untyped_return] genuine: fetchJson returns Promise<unknown> but can return null. Change to Promise<unknown | null>.\n\n[review::.::holistic::type_safety::unused_interface_field] genuine: RepoResponse.language validated but never read by fetchRepoData. Remove it.\n\n[review::.::holistic::test_strategy::untested_fetch_functions] genuine: fetchRepoData/fetchAllRepoData have zero test coverage. Add mocked fetch tests.\n\n[review::.::holistic::test_strategy::untested_server_load] genuine but low priority: load function is thin delegation. Testing fetchRepoData provides more value.\n\n[review::.::holistic::convention_outlier::mixed_lifecycle_pattern] genuine: Terminal.svelte uses onMount while +page.svelte uses $effect. Migrate Terminal to $effect for runes consistency.\n\n[review::.::holistic::naming_quality::fetchJson_hides_null] genuine: rename to tryFetchJson to communicate nullable return.\n\n[review::.::holistic::ai_generated_debt::uniform_description_prose] genuine but low priority: content/style decision for portfolio owner.\n\n[review::.::holistic::api_surface_coherence::internal_helpers_exported_for_testing] genuine: helpers exported for testability. Add comment noting intent.\n\n[review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::parallel_project_imports] genuine: both server and page import from projects. Reasonable SvelteKit pattern for static data. Medium priority.\n\n[review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::github_data_merge_in_presentation] genuine: attachGithubData could move to server but adds serialization complexity. Medium priority.",
